headline: Nvidia Partner, Rival Lead S&P 500 Stocks Monday
summary: Super Micro Computer, Advanced Micro Devices, Diamondback Energy, Nike and Williams-Sonoma were the top five S&P 500 index gainers on the stock market today. Super Micro stock surged 10.2% to 60.05 on Monday, setting a fresh six-month high.

headline: Williams-Sonoma (WSM) Stock Trades Up, Here Is Why
summary: Shares of kitchenware and home goods retailer Williams-Sonoma (NYSE:WSM) jumped 3.2% in the afternoon session after its West Elm brand announced an expanded collaboration with fashion designer Joseph Altuzarra for a new kids' collection. The collection, which launched on the same day as the stock's rise, was inspired by the designer's children and featured nature-inspired, hand-drawn botanical designs on items like furniture, bedding, and rugs. headline: WEST ELM EXPANDS PARTNERSHIP WITH JOSEPH ALTUZARRA
summary: BROOKLYN, NY, July 28, 2025--Global design company West Elm, a portfolio brand of Williams-Sonoma, Inc.
